  <title>Getting started</title>
  
  <p>This page describes how to get started using <app>PoProofRead</app>.</p>

  <section id="starting_opening">
    <title>Opening the podiff-file</title>
    <p>First download the file you wish to work with,
    e.g. "<file>example.podiff</file>". There are now three different
    ways that you can open the file:</p>
    <list>
      <item><p>Start <app>PoProofRead</app> and use the <gui>Open</gui> file
      dialog (Ctrl-o)</p></item>
      <item><p>Right click the "<file>example.podiff</file>" file in
      your file browser and find <app>PoProofRead</app> among the
      applications in the <gui>Open with</gui>-menu</p></item>
      <item><p>Start <app>PoProofRead</app> from the terminal and
      supply the file as a argument e.g: <cmd>poproofread-gtk
      example.podiff</cmd></p></item>
    </list>
  </section>

  <section id="starting_gui">
    <title>The <app>PoProofRead</app> main window</title>
    <p>The figure below shows the <app>PoProofRead</app> main windown. Moving from the top down it consist of:</p>
    <terms>
      <item>
	<title>The navigation bar</title>
	<p>From left to right it contains controls for setting and
	jumping to a bookmark, activating the in-line commenting mode,
	navigating through the diff parts or jumping to a specific
	diff part.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
	<title>The diff and comment fields</title>
	<p>The top and bottom fields in the center are used for
	showing the diff and typing in the comment, respectively. In
	in-line mode the comment field will expand and use all of the
	space.</p>
      </item>
      <item>
	<title>The status line</title>
	<p>This bottom line shows the status of the proofreading.</p>
      </item>
    </terms>
